The paper deals with efficient inference in Dynamic Bayesian Networks, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on exploiting persistence in the network structure suggests a potential fit for the data mining (cs.DM) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the use of algorithms and asymptotic bounds suggests a possible fit for the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
